    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "An HR department needs to process job applications by shifting email addresses to rearrange the order of applications before reviewing them.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">Job</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">shiftEmails()</code> method that takes an integer <code>shiftAmount</code> as a parameter and shifts the list of extracted email addresses to the left by that number of positions.\r\n1. Loop shiftAmount times to shift emails one position at a time.\r\n2. Store the first email in a temporary variable before shifting.\r\n3. Move each email forward in the list.\r\n4. Move the first email to the last position after shifting is complete.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">JobRunner</code> class:\r\n\r\nCall the <code>shiftEmails()</code> method with a shift amount to modify the list.\r\nPrint the shifted list using the <code>resultsToString()</code> method.\r\n\r\n<details style=\"background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;\">\r\n    <summary style=\"font-size: 1.2em; font-weight: bold;\">🔦 Need help with your algorithm?</summary>\r\n    <div style=\"margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;\">\r\n    \t<p>Here is one approach to solving this problem.</p>\r\n        <pre style=\"background-color: #333333; color: white;\">\r\nDeclare and initialize a variable shiftAmount to determine how many positions to shift\r\n&nbsp\r\nLoop shiftAmount number of times:\r\n   Store the first email in a temporary variable\r\n   Loop through the list of emails, shifting each email one position to the left\r\n   Set the last email in the list to the temporary variable\r\n&nbsp\r\nReturn the modified list of emails\r\n</pre>\r\n    </div>\r\n</details>",
